messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/users

HTTP methods (based on the code):
- allMethods: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In server.js the users router is mounted with: app.use('/api/users', userRoutes); so the router paths are prefixed with /api/users.
- In routes/userRoutes.js the route for '/' is defined as:
  - router.route('/').post(registerUser).get(protect, admin, getUsers);
  This registers POST and GET handlers on the path '/'. With the router prefix that becomes POST /api/users and GET /api/users.
- The registerUser controller handles POST /api/users (it is the POST handler attached to '/').
- There are no explicit router.all(...) or any mechanism in the code that would allow all HTTP methods, so allMethods is false.
- HEAD is not explicitly registered in the code; per your instruction I did not assume implicit framework behavior, so HEAD is false.
- OPTIONS and TRACE are not defined anywhere in the code for this path, so they are false.
- PUT, DELETE and PATCH are not defined for the '/api/users' path (they are defined for other paths like '/api/users/:id' or '/api/users/profile'), so they are false for this path.
- GET is true because a GET handler is explicitly registered on the same path (GET /api/users is getUsers, protected by middleware).
